This paper deals with natural language generation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks for encoding and generating text is also a common technique in natural language processing and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper deals with generating summaries from knowledge base triples. Finally, the use of DBpedia and Wikidata triples suggests a connection to databases and data management (cs.DB).
